Vol / Page:  11
Edition:
Quote:  The <i>tauas</i>, or war parties, rapidly decreased [with the advent of Christianity] in number, and those chiefs who could before muster a force of five or six hundred men, were afterwards satisfied with two hundred, and thus from the want of followers their contests gradually ceased, and with them their horrid feasts. <i>Ibid.</i> 272 A few weeks only elapsed before a taua arrived to revenge their deaths.
